#eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - ANC deputy secretary in Mpumalanga, Lindiwe Ntshalintshali says the party will be going through it database to ensure that every member has been vetted. This after the party revoked Philemon Lukhele’s membership over his alleged involvement in the kidnapping and murder of Hillary Gardee. She was the daughter of former EFF secretary-general Godrich Gardee. READ: Mpumalanga ANC withdraws Lukhele's membership Ntshalintshali says an internal investigation has revealed that Lukhele obtained his membershing irregularly. That he did not qualify for membership as he was not a South African citizen. Watch the video above for more details on this story.